text: Callaway County is a county located in the U.S. state of Missouri. In the 2020 U.S. Census, the county's population was 44,283. Its county seat is Fulton. It is named for Captain James Callaway, grandson of Daniel Boone. ==References== ==Other websites== *Callaway County official website Category:1820 establishments in Missouri Territory
